btree-kotlin
============

A Kotlin Multiplatform port of `std::collections::BTreeMap` and
`std::collections::BTreeSet` from the Rust standard library
(`library/alloc/src/collections/btree/`).

The Rust upstream is dual-licensed Apache-2.0 OR MIT, copyright
The Rust Project Developers. The Kotlin translation here is a
derivative work, distributed under the same dual Apache-2.0 OR MIT
terms. All algorithmic and structural design credit — the B-tree of
order 6, the Handle/NodeRef cursor scheme, the underflow-handling
fixup logic, the iterator state machines — belongs to the upstream
contributors.

Vendored Rust source is fetched into `tmp/rust-stdlib-collections-btree/`
by `tools/fetch-rust-source.sh` and is not tracked in this repo
(see `.gitignore`). The Kotlin port lives at
`src/commonMain/kotlin/io/github/kotlinmania/btree_kotlin/`. Each
ported `.kt` file carries a `// port-lint:` header pointing at the
specific Rust source path it was translated from, plus a short
attribution preamble naming the upstream copyright holder and the
dual license.

