Translation rules — see CLAUDE.md and PORTING.md. The short version:
line-by-line transliteration; `MaybeUninit<T>` becomes nullable Kotlin
storage; raw pointers / `NonNull<T>` become regular references;
`unsafe` boundaries are marked but otherwise dissolve under the
Kotlin GC; iterators round-trip through Kotlin's standard
`Iterator<T>` / `MutableIterator<T>` interfaces; the public
`BTreeMap<K, V>` / `BTreeSet<T>` types implement
`MutableMap<K, V>` / `MutableSet<T>` so callers downstream can use
them anywhere a Kotlin map/set is expected.
